# Enterprise CRM Platform

## Overview

Build an enterprise-grade Customer Relationship Management (CRM) platform that enables organizations to manage customers, contacts, sales opportunities, tasks, communications, reporting, and team collaboration from a single system.

The platform must support multiple user roles, role-based permissions, auditability, reporting, and enterprise-scale operations.

The goal is to improve customer management, sales efficiency, team productivity, and business visibility.

---

## Business Objectives

- Centralize customer and contact information.
- Track customer interactions and activities.
- Manage sales opportunities through configurable pipelines.
- Improve collaboration across teams.
- Provide actionable business insights through dashboards and reports.
- Ensure accountability through audit trails.
- Enable secure access control based on user roles.

---

## User Roles

### System Administrator

Responsible for managing users, permissions, system settings, workflows, and configurations.

### Sales Manager

Responsible for overseeing sales teams, monitoring pipelines, assigning opportunities, reviewing performance, and generating reports.

### Sales Representative

Responsible for managing leads, customers, contacts, opportunities, activities, and tasks.

### Support Representative

Responsible for viewing customer information, recording interactions, and managing support-related activities.

### Read-Only User

Can access information according to permissions but cannot modify data.

